      "span_text": "As an example of this, [CITATION_1] found that TI in larvae of the damselfly Ischnura elegans was more likely to be utilised in staged laboratory encounters with predators if an alternate anti-predator defence was negated by removal of lamellae; otherwise, lamellae can be sacrificed through autotomy, as an escape strategy, when grasped by a predator."
